# SSH public keys authorized to connect to open-seer's modal agents
# (sweep-* and fixer-* machines).
#
# open-seer runs all agents under the shared MNGR_USER_ID "open-seer", so the
# keys below are installed on every fixer image at spawn (DESIGN.md §2, §9).
# The connect command for each fixer is posted as a comment on its Sentry
# issue.
#
# To add yourself: run (from the open-seer repo root; the script imports mngr
# internals, so it runs in your mngr checkout's environment)
#   uv run --project <path-to-mngr-checkout> python scripts/setup_debug_access.py
# and append the printed public key as a new line below. Open a PR.
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#
# To debug after your key is merged:
#   MNGR_HOST_DIR=~/.mngr-open-seer mngr list
#   MNGR_HOST_DIR=~/.mngr-open-seer mngr connect <agent-id>
